title: Specifications that define WebIDL content (WHATWG perspective)
description: This crawl includes specifications that define WebIDL content, preferring WHATWG specifications to W3C specifications when both exist.

touch-action.name: touch-action
touch-action.value: auto | none | [ [ pan-x | pan-left | pan-right ] || [ pan-y | pan-up | pan-down ] || pinch-zoom ] | manipulation
touch-action.appliesTo: all elements except: non-replaced inline elements, table rows, row groups, table columns, and column groups.

animation-composition.name: animation-composition
animation-composition.computedValue: list, each item a keyword as specified

results.title: CSS Backgrounds and Borders Module Level 4

background-position-x.name: background-position-x
background-position-x.percentages: refer to width of background positioning area minus width of background image
background-position-x.computedValue: A list, each item consisting of: an offset given as a combination of an absolute length and a percentage, plus an origin keyword

background-position-y.name: background-position-y
background-position-y.percentages: refer to height of background positioning area minus height of background image
background-position-y.computedValue: A list, each item consisting of: an offset given as a combination of an absolute length and a percentage, plus an origin keyword

background-position-inline.name: background-position-inline
background-position-inline.initial: not applicable (initial value comes from physical property)
background-position-inline.percentages: refer to inline-size of background positioning area minus inline-size of background image
background-position-inline.computedValue: A list, each item consisting of: an offset given as a combination of an absolute length and a percentage, plus an origin keyword

background-position-block.name: background-position-block
background-position-block.initial: not applicable (initial value comes from physical property)
background-position-block.percentages: refer to size of background positioning area minus size of background image
background-position-block.computedValue: A list, each item consisting of: an offset given as a combination of an absolute length and a percentage, plus an origin keyword

border-radius.name: border-radius
border-radius.appliesTo: all elements, except table element when border-collapse is collapse

corner-shape.name: corner-shape
corner-shape.appliesTo: all elements, except table element when border-collapse is collapse

border-limit.name: border-limit
border-limit.value: all | [ sides | corners ] <length-percentage>? | [ top | right | bottom | left ] <length-percentage>
border-limit.appliesTo: all elements, except table element when border-collapse is collapse

border-clip.name: border-clip
border-clip.percentages: refer to length of border-edge side
border-clip.computedValue: normal, or a list consisting of absolute lengths, or percentages as specified

border-clip-top.name: border-clip-top
border-clip-top.percentages: refer to length of border-edge side
border-clip-top.computedValue: normal, or a list consisting of absolute lengths, or percentages as specified

border-clip-right.name: border-clip-right
border-clip-right.percentages: refer to length of border-edge side
border-clip-right.computedValue: normal, or a list consisting of absolute lengths, or percentages as specified

border-clip-bottom.name: border-clip-bottom
border-clip-bottom.percentages: refer to length of border-edge side
border-clip-bottom.computedValue: normal, or a list consisting of absolute lengths, or percentages as specified

border-clip-left.name: border-clip-left
border-clip-left.percentages: refer to length of border-edge side
border-clip-left.computedValue: normal, or a list consisting of absolute lengths, or percentages as specified

<position>.value: [ [ left | center | right | top | bottom | start | end | <length-percentage> ] | [ left | center | right | x-start | x-end | <length-percentage> ] [ top | center | bottom | y-start | y-end | <length-percentage> ] | [ center | [ left | right | x-start | x-end ] <length-percentage>? ] && [ center | [ top | bottom | y-start | y-end ] <length-percentage>? ] | [ center | [ start | end ] <length-percentage>? ] [ center | [ start | end ] <length-percentage>? ] ]

margin-top.name: margin-top
margin-top.appliesTo: all elements except internal table elements
margin-top.percentages: refer to logical width of containing block
margin-top.computedValue: the keyword auto or a computed <length-percentage> value

margin-right.name: margin-right
margin-right.appliesTo: all elements except internal table elements
margin-right.percentages: refer to logical width of containing block
margin-right.computedValue: the keyword auto or a computed <length-percentage> value

margin-bottom.name: margin-bottom
margin-bottom.appliesTo: all elements except internal table elements
margin-bottom.percentages: refer to logical width of containing block
margin-bottom.computedValue: the keyword auto or a computed <length-percentage> value

margin-left.name: margin-left
margin-left.appliesTo: all elements except internal table elements

padding-right.percentages: refer to logical width of containing block

padding-left.percentages: refer to logical width of containing block

wrap-flow.value: auto | both | start | end | minimum | maximum | clear

results.title: CSS Generated Content for Paged Media Module Level 4

copy-into.name: copy-into
copy-into.appliesTo: all elements and pseudo-elements, but not ::first-line or ::first-letter.

scrollbar-color.name: scrollbar-color
scrollbar-color.computedValue: specified keyword or two computed colors

shape-inside.name: shape-inside
shape-inside.computedValue: computed lengths for <basic-shape>, the absolute URI for <uri>, otherwise as specified

<basic-shape>.prose: The shape is computed based on the values of one of inset(), circle(), ellipse() or polygon().

<uri>.prose: If the <uri> references an SVG shape element, that element defines the shape. Otherwise, if the <uri> references an image, the shape is extracted and computed based on the alpha channel of the specified image. If the <uri> does not reference an SVG shape element or an image, the effect is as if the value auto had been specified.

results.title: CSS Mobile Text Size Adjustment Module Level 1

<percentage>.prose: When displaying on a small device, renderers must not do size adjustment but instead the computed value of font-size must be multiplied by this percentage. Note: This means that 'text-size-adjust: 100%;' is equivalent to 'text-size-adjust: none;'.

aspect-ratio.name: aspect-ratio
aspect-ratio.appliesTo: all elements except inline boxes and internal ruby or table boxes
aspect-ratio.computedValue: specified keyword or a pair of numbers

translate.name: translate
translate.percentages: relative to the width of the containing block (for the first value) or the height (for the second value)
translate.computedValue: the keyword none or a pair of computed <length-percentage> values and optionally an absolute length
translate.animationType: by computed value, adding a third 0 value if needed to match components, but see below for none

rotate.name: rotate
rotate.computedValue: the keyword none, or an <angle> with an optional axis consisting of a list of three <number>s
rotate.animationType: as SLERP, but see below for none

scale.name: scale
scale.computedValue: the keyword none, or a list of 2 or 3 <number>s
scale.animationType: by computed value, but see below for none

perspective.name: perspective
perspective.computedValue: the keyword none or an absolute length

perspective-origin.name: perspective-origin
perspective-origin.percentages: refer to the size of the reference box

mix-blend-mode.name: mix-blend-mode
mix-blend-mode.appliesTo: All elements. In SVG, it applies to container elements, graphics elements and graphics referencing elements. [SVG11]

isolation.name: isolation
isolation.appliesTo: All elements. In SVG, it applies to container elements, graphics elements and graphics referencing elements. [SVG11]

<blend-mode>.value: normal | multiply | screen | overlay | darken | lighten | color-dodge |color-burn | hard-light | soft-light | difference | exclusion | hue | saturation | color | luminosity

<composite-mode>.value: clear | copy | source-over | destination-over | source-in | destination-in | source-out | destination-out | source-atop | destination-atop | xor | lighter | plus-darker | plus-lighter

backdrop-filter.name: backdrop-filter
backdrop-filter.appliesTo: All elements. In SVG, it applies to container elements without the defs element and all graphics elements
